Author: jl777c#5810
Content: ripple has what are called validator nodes

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: these nodes have total power over the blockchain, create blocks, censor tx, freeze accounts, likely even edit prior tx details

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: for many years ripple had 8 validator nodes, all run by ripple

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: so a distributed infrastructure with centralized control

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: since these validator nodes are all powerful, you cant really let just anybody become a validator. else they can really mess things up with these great powers

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: so all the new validator nodes add a list of trusted validators, which they use to resolve conflicts

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: it seems all the stellar validator nodes went offline (centralized control over validators), maybe somebody pulled the plug on the power by mistake, who knows

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: since the only trusted validators were offline, the other validators had no idea what to do, so they shutdown waiting for instructions from their masters
